      "content": "but it's not just about making things \"more intuitive.\" it feels targeted. like it's not just a general feature, but they are actively monitoring my specific reactions to see how i respond to certain stimuli. if they can do this with just light and temp, they could basically run psychological profiles on me in my own house without me ever knowing. how easy would it be for a big tech company to actually deploy something like that on a private individual for data collection or testing purposes?",
